Reciprocity: Giving a discount or incentive for compliance. Offering a complimentary repair or maintenance plan might help sell an old clunker. Reciprocity underlies this method. Social proof: Influencing conduct via seeing others. Using customer testimonials to sell an outdated car may work. This technique uses social proof. Scarcity: Making an object seem scarce to boost its value. Emphasizing the car's strong demand and little supply may help sell an outdated clunker. Scarcity psychology underlies this method. Authority: Persuading with authority or competence. Highlighting the seller's auto business expertise may help sell an old junk. Authority is the psychology of this method. These tactics are not necessarily ethical, depending on the circumstances and implementation. 